                    <head>Munajat</head>
                    <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104964 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/nr96038220">
                        <summary/>
                        <msItem>
                            <author key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80013285">
                                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80013285">Anṣārī al-Harawī, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 1006-1089</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="" key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80013285">Khwājah ‘Abd Allāh Anṣārī Harav</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara" key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80013285" type="supplied">انصارى الهروى، عبد الله بن محمد</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Munājāt</title>
                            <title xml:lang="per">مناجات</title>
                            <note>
                                <p>The Munājāt, or intimate discourses with God, also known by the title <title>Ilahī-nāmah</title>, wholly or partly by Khwājah ‘Abd Allāh Anṣārī Haravī (396-481/1006-1088). </p>
                                <p>The present manuscript is an outstanding calligraphic copied by <name type="person" role="scribe">Mīr ‘Imād al-Ḥasanī</name>. Dated <name type="place">Tabriz</name> (bi-Dār al-salṭanat Tabrīz), 990/1582.</p>
                                <p>Other contents: 1r, ownership inscriptions, one describing the work as Maqālāt-i Khvājah ‘Abd Allāh Anṣārī on 8 folios, and one dated 1272/1855-6; and seal impressions. 1v, fainter seal impressions. </p>
                                <p>Title supplied. </p>
                            </note>
                            <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
